        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 1:23PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 123 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mt Pleasant, or 11 miles west of Albemarle, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Badin Lake, Plyler, Locust, Badin, Stanfield, Richfield,
New London, Fish Tales Marina, and Morrow Mountain State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
